President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump have announced additional details for the 139th White House Easter Egg Roll, which will take place on April 17, 2017, on the South Lawn of the White House. Tickets for the event can be requested through an online lottery, which opened on March 15 and will close on March 18. The lottery is free to enter, and winners will be notified via email on March 31. The commemorative eggs for this year's event will also be available for purchase online. The White House Easter Egg Roll is a longstanding tradition that dates back to 1878, and the President and First Lady are proud to continue this tradition while also adding new ones to the history of the nation.